December 2, 2020 | https://h.shadowtime2000.com/what-are-js-generators | <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/*/https://h.shadowtime2000.com/what-are-js-generators">archive.org</a>
<br/><!-- hnss:readable-content --><hr/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><section itemprop="articleBody mainEntityOfPage"><div><div><div><div><p>Subscribe to <!-- -->my<!-- --> newsletter and never miss <!-- -->my<!-- --> upcoming articles</p></div></div></div><div itemprop="text">
<p>Generators are a feature in Javascript which are basically functions that are kind of like iterators.</p>
<h2 id="creating">Creating</h2>
<p>You can create generators like this:</p>
<pre><code><span><span>function</span>* <span>myGenerator</span>(<span></span>) </span>{}
</code></pre>
<p>The <code>*</code> after <code>function</code> is required.</p>
<h2 id="yielding">Yielding</h2>
<p>The core mechanic of generators is <code>yield</code>ing values.</p>
<pre><code><span><span>function</span>* <span>myGenerator</span>(<span></span>) </span>{
    <span>yield</span> <span>1</span>;
    <span>yield</span> <span>"foo"</span>;
    <span>yield</span> <span>"bar"</span>;
    <span>yield</span> { <span>thing</span>: <span>true</span> };
}
</code></pre>
<h2 id="taking-values">Taking Values</h2>
<p>You have created your generator. Now, we need to use it. When you have a generator, you can call <code>.next()</code> on it, and it will run the generator until it reaches a <code>yield</code> statement. When it reaches it, it will return an object with two parameters, <code>value</code>, and <code>done</code>.</p>
<pre><code><span>const</span> one = myGenerator.next().value; 
<span>const</span> foo = myGenerator.next().value; 
<span>const</span> bar = myGenerator.next().value; 
<span>const</span> thingTrue = myGenerator.next().value; 
</code></pre>
<h2 id="mdn-docs">MDN Docs</h2>
<p>You can look more into generators <a target="_blank" href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Generator">on the MDN docs</a>.</p>
</div></div></section></div></div>

